@startuml
title User Service JPA Entities Overview

hide empty members
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false

top to bottom direction
scale 800 width

skinparam class {
  BorderThickness<<EntityView>> 3
  BorderColor<<EntityView>> #1F618D
  RoundCorner<<EntityView>> 15
}

' ===== ACCESS CONTROL =====
package "Access Control Domain" {
  class DomainEntity <<Entity>>
  class BusinessUnitEntity <<Entity>>
  class UserEntity <<Entity>>
  class BusinessUnitUserEntity <<Entity>>
  class BusinessUnitUserRoleEntity <<Entity>>
  class RoleEntity <<EntityView>>
}

' ===== AUDIT =====
package "Audit and Event Logging" {
  class BusinessEventEntity <<Entity>>
  class LogActionEntity <<Entity>>
  class LogAuditDetailEntity <<Entity>>
}

' =====================================================

DomainEntity -[hidden]down-> BusinessUnitEntity
BusinessUnitEntity -[hidden]down-> BusinessUnitUserEntity
BusinessUnitUserEntity -[hidden]down-> BusinessUnitUserRoleEntity
UserEntity -[hidden]right-> BusinessUnitUserEntity
RoleEntity -[hidden]right-> BusinessUnitUserRoleEntity
BusinessEventEntity -[hidden]down-> LogAuditDetailEntity

' =====================================================

DomainEntity ||--o{ BusinessUnitEntity
DomainEntity ||--o{ RoleEntity

BusinessUnitEntity }o--o| BusinessUnitEntity
BusinessUnitEntity ||--o{ BusinessUnitUserEntity
UserEntity ||--o{ BusinessUnitUserEntity

BusinessUnitUserEntity ||--o{ BusinessUnitUserRoleEntity
RoleEntity ||--o{ BusinessUnitUserRoleEntity

UserEntity ||--o{ BusinessEventEntity
UserEntity ||--o{ BusinessEventEntity

LogActionEntity ||--o{ LogAuditDetailEntity
BusinessUnitEntity ||--o{ LogAuditDetailEntity
UserEntity ..> LogAuditDetailEntity

note bottom of RoleEntity
Maps to the v_current_roles database view,
not directly to the base roles table.
end note

note bottom of BusinessEventEntity
The schema has foreign keys from subject_user_id
and initiator_user_id to users.user_id.
The entity currently stores those as scalar IDs.
end note

note bottom of LogAuditDetailEntity
Only logAction and businessUnit are mapped as JPA associations.
userId is stored as a scalar field in the entity.
end note

@enduml
